cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel deep learning architecture for automated quantitative measurement of the spine from MR images. This involves estimating multiple indices such as heights, widths, and areas of vertebral bodies and discs. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method involves the use of a cascade amplifier network and local shape-constrained manifold regularization loss function, which are both deep learning techniques. Therefore, the paper is also likely to belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The experiments involve the use of MR images, which is a type of medical imaging, and the paper proposes a method for clinical spinal disease diagnoses. Therefore, the paper is also likely to belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
